1
00:00:03,223 --> 00:00:06,690
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A MAN WHO DIED.

2
00:00:06,690 --> 00:00:10,623
ALL THE STORIES THE MAN SPUN
CAME TRUE,

3
00:00:10,623 --> 00:00:13,790
SO THE KING, THE NOBILITY,
AND THE KINGDOM'S RICH

4
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:17,990
ALL WENT TO HIM TO GET HIM
TO WRITE THEM STORIES.

5
00:00:17,990 --> 00:00:20,556
BUT WHEN THEY SAW THEIR WISHES
GRANTED,

6
00:00:20,556 --> 00:00:23,556
STARK TERROR
OF HIS POWER SEIZED THEM,

7
00:00:23,556 --> 00:00:26,256
AND THEY BEGAN TO ABHOR HIM.

8
00:00:26,256 --> 00:00:28,756
WHEN THE MAN FINALLY DIED,

9
00:00:28,756 --> 00:00:30,556
THE PEOPLE REJOICED

10
00:00:30,556 --> 00:00:33,823
THAT THIS WELLSPRING
OF MISFORTUNE HAD DRIED UP.

11
00:00:33,823 --> 00:00:35,990
NO ONE HEARD THE ECHOING SOUND

12
00:00:35,990 --> 00:00:38,856
OF THE DEAD MAN'S
SCORNFUL LAUGHTER.

13
00:00:40,823 --> 00:00:43,356
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

14
00:00:55,396 --> 00:00:58,430
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

15
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:27,330
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

16
00:02:10,436 --> 00:02:13,503
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"FINAL WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

17
00:02:30,713 --> 00:02:32,413
-DID MYTHO GET TO GO BACK
TO BEING THE PRINCE?

18
00:02:32,413 --> 00:02:34,446
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "DANCE OF
THE SUGAR PLUM FAIRY" PLAYING ]

19
00:02:34,446 --> 00:02:36,379
HE DEFEATED THE RAVEN'S BLOOD!

20
00:02:36,379 --> 00:02:41,046
I GET IT --
FAKIR WROTE A STORY ABOUT MYTHO.

21
00:02:41,046 --> 00:02:44,513
OH, AND RUE WENT BACK
TO BEING RUE, TOO!

22
00:02:44,513 --> 00:02:46,779
I'M SO GLAD!

23
00:02:46,779 --> 00:02:48,679
I'M SO GLAD.

24
00:02:48,679 --> 00:02:51,819
EVERYBODY LOOKS
LIKE THEY'RE HAVING FUN.

25
00:02:51,819 --> 00:02:55,753
I WANT TO DANCE WITH THEM, TOO!
QUACK?

26
00:02:55,753 --> 00:02:58,619
OH, SO,
I WENT BACK TO BEING A DUCK?

27
00:02:58,619 --> 00:03:00,286
QUACK.

28
00:03:00,286 --> 00:03:03,319
RIGHT, THE PRINCE GOT
ALL OF HIS HEART BACK.

29
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:06,919
SO THAT MEANS PRINCESS TUTU'S
ROLE IS FINISHED.

30
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:10,819
I'VE GONE BACK
TO BEING A PLAIN OLD DUCK.

31
00:03:10,819 --> 00:03:16,419
FAKIR, RUE, MYTHO.

32
00:03:16,419 --> 00:03:20,586
IT LOOKS LIKE I WASN'T ABLE
TO HELP THE PRINCE AT ALL.

33
00:03:20,586 --> 00:03:24,019
I JUST WATCHED.

34
00:03:24,019 --> 00:03:26,119
HUH?

35
00:03:26,119 --> 00:03:29,353
[ "DANCE OF THE SUGAR PLUM
FAIRY" CONTINUES ]

36
00:03:29,353 --> 00:03:30,753
[ GASPS ]

37
00:03:30,753 --> 00:03:31,986
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

38
00:03:31,986 --> 00:03:35,019
SO, THAT WAS A DREAM?

39
00:03:35,019 --> 00:03:38,819
[ "DANCE OF THE SUGAR PLUM
FAIRY" CONCLUDES ]

40
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:40,753
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

41
00:03:40,753 --> 00:03:42,819
[ BELL TOLLS ]

42
00:03:42,819 --> 00:03:44,986
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

43
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:51,026
I WONDER IF FAKIR FINISHED
HIS STORY ABOUT MYTHO.

44
00:03:51,026 --> 00:03:54,026
WHAT KIND OF STORY
WILL HE MAKE IT?

45
00:03:54,026 --> 00:03:56,726
I WONDER IF I'LL BE IN IT, TOO.
HUH?

46
00:03:56,726 --> 00:03:58,726
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

47
00:03:58,726 --> 00:04:01,193
IS THAT FAKIR?

48
00:04:10,293 --> 00:04:13,093
YOU DOING RESEARCH?
-YES.

49
00:04:13,093 --> 00:04:15,993
-OH! SO, UM...

50
00:04:15,993 --> 00:04:19,093
DID YOU WRITE A STORY ABOUT MY--

51
00:04:19,093 --> 00:04:20,493
WHOA!

52
00:04:20,493 --> 00:04:23,593
-NO, I HAVEN'T WRITTEN IT YET.

53
00:04:23,593 --> 00:04:24,993
-OH, WELL, THAT'S OKAY.

54
00:04:24,993 --> 00:04:26,959
THEN, DO YOU WANT
TO GET STARTED ON IT NOW?

55
00:04:26,959 --> 00:04:28,859
THE FASTER WE HELP MYTHO, RIGHT?

56
00:04:28,859 --> 00:04:32,859
-IT'S NOT THAT EVERYTHING
I WRITE COMES TRUE.

57
00:04:32,859 --> 00:04:35,359
AND I DON'T EVEN KNOW YET

58
00:04:35,359 --> 00:04:37,826
WHETHER OR NOT I STILL
HAVE THE SAME POWER.

59
00:04:39,693 --> 00:04:42,659
-I-I'M SURE
IT'LL TURN OUT JUST FINE.

60
00:04:42,659 --> 00:04:44,826
I MEAN, IF YOU WISH
"I WANT TO HELP MYTHO"

61
00:04:44,826 --> 00:04:46,093
REALLY HARD AS YOU WRITE,

62
00:04:46,093 --> 00:04:48,193
THIS TIME YOU'LL SUCCEED
FOR SURE AND --

63
00:04:48,193 --> 00:04:49,499
[ GASPS ] I'M SORRY, FAKIR.

64
00:04:49,499 --> 00:04:50,999
WHEN I SAID "THIS TIME,"

65
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:53,299
I DIDN'T MEAN THAT TIME WHEN
YOUR FATHER AND MOTHER WERE --

66
00:04:53,299 --> 00:04:55,899
UM, SO, YOU SEE...

67
00:04:55,899 --> 00:04:59,699
I'M SORRY.

68
00:04:59,699 --> 00:05:01,199
-MM.

69
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:04,199
-[ Thinking ] OHH, I'M STUPID,
STUPID, STUPID!

70
00:05:04,199 --> 00:05:05,933
FAKIR SAID HE'D WRITE IT,

71
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:08,366
BUT I HAD TO GO GET
ALL IMPATIENT AND DO THAT.

72
00:05:08,366 --> 00:05:09,699
[ SPARKLE! ]

73
00:05:09,699 --> 00:05:11,466
HUH? HELLO?

74
00:05:11,466 --> 00:05:12,499
OH.

75
00:05:12,499 --> 00:05:14,566
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

76
00:05:14,566 --> 00:05:16,466
WHAT?

77
00:05:17,799 --> 00:05:19,866
-MR. FAKIR
FROM THE BALLET DIVISION,

78
00:05:19,866 --> 00:05:21,566
YOU WANT TO CHECK OUT
THESE FIVE BOOKS?

79
00:05:21,566 --> 00:05:23,733
-YES.
-OH, AND THAT BOOK OVER THERE?

80
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:24,966
-WHAT?

81
00:05:24,966 --> 00:05:27,299
-I WAS ASKED TO GIVE IT TO YOU
IF YOU CAME.

82
00:05:27,299 --> 00:05:28,699
-TO ME?

83
00:05:28,699 --> 00:05:31,366
-MR. AUTOR FROM
THE MUSIC DIVISION ASKED ME.

84
00:05:31,366 --> 00:05:32,733
-I DON'T KNOW HIM.

85
00:05:32,733 --> 00:05:35,466
-OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I THOUGHT SO.

86
00:05:35,466 --> 00:05:37,099
-WHAT IS IT?
-NOTHING MUCH.

87
00:05:37,099 --> 00:05:38,966
IT'S STRANGE THAT MR. AUTOR
HAS BORROWED

88
00:05:38,966 --> 00:05:41,033
ALL FIVE OF THESE BOOKS BEFORE.
-WHAT?

89
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:42,099
-WHOA!

90
00:05:42,099 --> 00:05:44,133
-[ Thinking ] "AUTOR"?

91
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,866
WHO IS HE?

92
00:05:45,866 --> 00:05:47,599
-ALL RIGHT, THEN, EVERYBODY.

93
00:05:47,599 --> 00:05:50,573
I'LL PASS THEM OUT IN TURN,
SO PLEASE LINE UP.

94
00:05:50,573 --> 00:05:52,639
-HEY, DUCK, YOU
LOOK LIKE YOU'RE SPACING OUT.

95
00:05:52,639 --> 00:05:56,173
I BET YOU WERE SO HAPPY YOU
COULDN'T SLEEP LAST NIGHT, HUH?

96
00:05:56,173 --> 00:05:58,106
-HUH? HAPPY ABOUT WHAT?

97
00:05:58,106 --> 00:06:02,573
-OH, SHE'S ALWAYS SPACED OUT,
BUT WE'LL LET IT GO.

98
00:06:02,573 --> 00:06:05,106
-'CAUSE TODAY'S HER LONG-AWAITED
FIRST POINTE LESSON!

99
00:06:05,106 --> 00:06:07,506
-POINTE LESSON? IS IT REALLY?

100
00:06:07,506 --> 00:06:09,206
-POINTE --
WHAT EVERY GIRL DREAMS

101
00:06:09,206 --> 00:06:11,773
FROM THE DAY THAT SHE DECIDES
TO BECOME A BALLERINA!

102
00:06:11,773 --> 00:06:13,539
-THE LONGED-FOR TASTE
OF BROKEN NAILS

103
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:15,439
AND PAINFUL BLOOD BLISTERS!

104
00:06:15,439 --> 00:06:16,906
-CORRECT!
[ ALL GASP ]

105
00:06:16,906 --> 00:06:19,339
AND THAT'S WHY I CAN'T HAVE
YOU TAKING THE FLIPPANT ATTITUDE

106
00:06:19,339 --> 00:06:21,873
THAT LEADS TO TALKING IN CLASS,
YOU HEAR ME?!

107
00:06:21,873 --> 00:06:23,306
-BOTH: YES, SIR.

108
00:06:23,306 --> 00:06:25,773
-NOW, MS. LILIE, YOUR TOE SHOES.

109
00:06:25,773 --> 00:06:27,039
-SIR!

110
00:06:27,039 --> 00:06:29,306
-FINALLY!
-[ Thinking ] TOE SHOES.

111
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:34,639
WHEN I'M TUTU, I CAN DO POINTE
LIKE IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

112
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:37,806
BUT I WONDER IF A DAY WILL COME
WHEN I CAN DANCE A PAS DE DEUX

113
00:06:37,806 --> 00:06:40,306
WITH THE PRINCE LIKE THAT
WHILE I'M DUCK.

114
00:06:40,306 --> 00:06:43,339
-MS. DUCK.
-UH, YES, SIR?

115
00:06:43,339 --> 00:06:44,973
-I AM SORRY, BUT AT THE MOMENT,

116
00:06:44,973 --> 00:06:47,773
I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T GIVE YOU TOE SHOES.

117
00:06:47,773 --> 00:06:50,579
-HUH?
-YOUR CONCENTRATION, MS. DUCK,

118
00:06:50,579 --> 00:06:53,279
HAS BEEN LACKING
EVEN MORE THAN BEFORE,

119
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:56,079
AS IF YOU'VE EVEN LOST
YOUR EAGERNESS.

120
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:58,979
IS IT POSSIBLE
YOU'VE COME TO THE CONCLUSION

121
00:06:58,979 --> 00:07:00,779
THAT YOU CAN'T DO ANYTHING,

122
00:07:00,779 --> 00:07:03,713
AND SO AS A RESULT,
YOU'VE DECIDED TO STOP TRYING

123
00:07:03,713 --> 00:07:05,479
TO MOVE FORWARD ALTOGETHER?

124
00:07:05,479 --> 00:07:07,079
-UM, WELL, I...

125
00:07:07,079 --> 00:07:10,446
IF I REALLY COULD HELP MYTHO
BY MYSELF, FAKIR,

126
00:07:10,446 --> 00:07:12,113
I WOULDN'T BE ASKING YOU!

127
00:07:12,113 --> 00:07:14,813
BUT RIGHT NOW
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

128
00:07:14,813 --> 00:07:18,813
[ Thinking ] WHAT <i>CAN</i> I DO?

129
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,546
-I'M WORRIED.
-HUH?

130
00:07:20,546 --> 00:07:22,079
-I TRULY AM WORRIED.

131
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:26,079
I FEAR YOUR DESIRE TO MARRY ME
HAS CAUSED YOU TO BE

132
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:28,079
DELIBERATELY REMISS
ABOUT YOUR LESSONS!

133
00:07:28,079 --> 00:07:29,246
-THAT'S NONSENSE!
-AAH!

134
00:07:29,246 --> 00:07:31,579
-MARRYING YOU IS TOO GREAT
OF AN HONOR.

135
00:07:31,579 --> 00:07:34,046
DUCK WOULD BE AFRAID
TO EVEN THINK OF IT!

136
00:07:34,046 --> 00:07:38,346
-[ YOWLING ]

137
00:07:38,346 --> 00:07:41,213
MS. DUCK, PLEASE WATCH
EVERYONE ELSE'S PRACTICE TODAY.

138
00:07:41,213 --> 00:07:42,413
-YES, SIR!

139
00:07:42,413 --> 00:07:44,646
[ ALL WHIMPERING ]

140
00:07:44,646 --> 00:07:47,013
-[ Strained ] I'M...GONNA DIE!

141
00:07:47,013 --> 00:07:49,719
-SO, THIS IS THE PAIN
OF POINTE, HUH?

142
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,653
I WISH DUCK COULD SHARE THIS.

143
00:07:51,653 --> 00:07:53,286
-I'M ALWAYS WATCHING.

144
00:07:53,286 --> 00:07:56,453
EVEN WHEN FAKIR'S TRYING HARD,
I'M JUST WATCHING.

145
00:07:56,453 --> 00:07:58,719
MAYBE THAT DREAM WAS PROPHETIC.

146
00:07:58,719 --> 00:08:01,719
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]
[ PIANO PLAYING ]

147
00:08:01,719 --> 00:08:04,186
-[ Thinking ]
A GUY FROM THE MUSIC DIVISION?

148
00:08:04,186 --> 00:08:06,219
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

149
00:08:06,219 --> 00:08:07,853
[ PLAYING CONTINUES ]

150
00:08:07,853 --> 00:08:10,719
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

151
00:08:10,719 --> 00:08:12,719
-YOU'RE LATE.

152
00:08:12,719 --> 00:08:14,219
[ CHUCKLES ]

153
00:08:14,219 --> 00:08:18,353
IT TOOK YOU 18 DAYS, 7 HOURS,
AND 24 MINUTES.

154
00:08:18,353 --> 00:08:19,919
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

155
00:08:19,919 --> 00:08:22,019
-THAT'S HOW LONG
IT TOOK FROM THE TIME

156
00:08:22,019 --> 00:08:25,019
YOU BEGAN TO RESEARCH YOUR POWER
UNTIL YOU NOTICED ME.

157
00:08:25,019 --> 00:08:27,286
[ PLAYING CONTINUES ]

158
00:08:27,286 --> 00:08:29,253
MR. FAKIR.

159
00:08:29,253 --> 00:08:31,753
-I TAKE IT YOU'RE AUTOR, THEN.

160
00:08:31,753 --> 00:08:33,686
WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

161
00:08:33,686 --> 00:08:36,819
-ASSUMED YOU HADN'T READ IT,
SO I SET IT ASIDE.

162
00:08:36,819 --> 00:08:38,319
I THINK YOU'LL FIND IT USEFUL

163
00:08:38,319 --> 00:08:40,753
FOR WHEN YOU START
WRITING YOUR STORIES.

164
00:08:40,753 --> 00:08:42,019
-OH, REALLY?

165
00:08:42,019 --> 00:08:43,753
AND WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

166
00:08:43,753 --> 00:08:46,753
-[ CHUCKLES ] EVERYTHING
YOU'VE BEEN DYING TO KNOW.

167
00:08:46,753 --> 00:08:47,786
-WHAT?

168
00:08:55,093 --> 00:08:56,093
-HUH?

169
00:08:56,093 --> 00:08:57,693
WHO WAS THAT?

170
00:09:01,659 --> 00:09:03,393
HUH?

171
00:09:03,393 --> 00:09:05,193
-[ Muffled ]
I'M ASKING YOU WHO YOU ARE.

172
00:09:05,193 --> 00:09:06,459
-FAKIR?

173
00:09:06,459 --> 00:09:09,259
-YOU'RE AS SHORT-TEMPERED
AS EVERYONE SAYS YOU ARE.

174
00:09:09,259 --> 00:09:11,459
BUT REMEMBER THIS,

175
00:09:11,459 --> 00:09:14,626
BRUTE FORCE HAS NO POWER
IN THE FACE OF WORDS.

176
00:09:14,626 --> 00:09:16,859
YOU WANT DROSSELMEYER'S POWER

177
00:09:16,859 --> 00:09:18,959
BECAUSE YOU'RE ALSO
AWARE OF THAT TRUTH, YES?

178
00:09:18,959 --> 00:09:21,193
-[ Thinking ]
DROSSELMEYER'S POWER?

179
00:09:21,193 --> 00:09:25,193
-THE POWER TO MAKE STORIES
INTO REALITY, IT'S SPLENDID,

180
00:09:25,193 --> 00:09:27,559
AND THE BOOKS THAT HAVE HAD
THEIR ENDINGS STOLEN

181
00:09:27,559 --> 00:09:30,593
BY THOSE WHO WISH TO STOP THEM
FROM BECOMING REALITY.

182
00:09:30,593 --> 00:09:32,559
ISN'T IT THRILLING?!

183
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,993
-YOU MEAN THEY TOOK OUT
THE ENDINGS

184
00:09:33,993 --> 00:09:36,093
TO STOP THEM FROM BECOMING REAL?

185
00:09:36,093 --> 00:09:37,426
-YES!

186
00:09:37,426 --> 00:09:39,493
-EVEN THOUGH THE ORIGINALS
ARE SEALED AWAY

187
00:09:39,493 --> 00:09:42,026
AND ALL WE CAN GET AHOLD OF
ARE THE COPIES.

188
00:09:42,026 --> 00:09:44,059
IMAGINE, A POWER SO STRONG

189
00:09:44,059 --> 00:09:47,593
THOSE ENDINGS
STILL HAD TO BE TORN OUT!

190
00:09:47,593 --> 00:09:50,133
IF YOU'RE SERIOUS
ABOUT ATTAINING THAT POWER,

191
00:09:50,133 --> 00:09:51,766
I WOULDN'T MIND YOU HELPING YOU,

192
00:09:51,766 --> 00:09:54,666
BUT YOU WILL HAVE TO FOLLOW
MY EVERY ORDER

193
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:57,766
AND BE PREPARED TO DIE
IF YOU SHOULD FAIL.

194
00:09:57,766 --> 00:10:00,399
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?!

195
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:02,899
"FOLLOW MY EVERY ORDER"?!
"BE PREPARED TO DIE"?!

196
00:10:02,899 --> 00:10:04,466
WHAT THE HECK
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?!

197
00:10:04,466 --> 00:10:06,633
WHY SHOULD HE HAVE
TO DO THOSE THINGS, HUH?!

198
00:10:06,633 --> 00:10:08,766
-I AM GIVING HIM A WARNING.
-HUH?

199
00:10:08,766 --> 00:10:11,266
-DO NOT TAKE
DROSSELMEYER'S POWER LIGHTLY.

200
00:10:11,266 --> 00:10:14,766
IF YOU USE IT IMPROPERLY,
THERE WILL BE HELL TO PAY.

201
00:10:14,766 --> 00:10:17,699
PEOPLE MAY EVEN DIE.

202
00:10:17,699 --> 00:10:19,766
-[ GASPS ]

203
00:10:19,766 --> 00:10:22,366
-YOU NEED TO BE PREPARED
FOR THAT POSSIBILITY.

204
00:10:22,366 --> 00:10:25,233
IF YOU WANT OUT,
I WON'T FORCE YOU.

205
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:28,133
-NO. TEACH ME.
-FAKIR!

206
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:29,733
-A WISE DECISION.

207
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:31,966
COME TO MY HOUSE TOMORROW.

208
00:10:31,966 --> 00:10:34,233
I'LL BE WAITING, FAKIR.

209
00:10:40,499 --> 00:10:42,366
-HE IS AWAKENED.
-THIS HERE IS DANGEROUS.

210
00:10:42,366 --> 00:10:44,666
-MUST DESTROY.
-THE QUEEN MUST TAKE STEPS.

211
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:46,533
-HE'S GONE TOO FAR.
-THEN LET US KILL --

212
00:10:46,533 --> 00:10:49,033
-NOW, NOW, HOLD ON!

213
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:51,573
IT SEEMS HE'S GAINED
THE KNOWLEDGE, BUT THAT'S ALL.

214
00:10:51,573 --> 00:10:55,006
IT WOULDN'T BE A BAD THING FOR
US TO WATCH FOR A LITTLE LONGER.

215
00:10:55,006 --> 00:10:56,673
NOTHING COULD BE BETTER

216
00:10:56,673 --> 00:10:59,339
THAN IF THIS MATTER
SETTLED ITSELF WITHOUT MISHAP.

217
00:10:59,339 --> 00:11:02,173
BUT IF NECESSARY,

218
00:11:02,173 --> 00:11:06,373
WE'LL TAKE STEPS WHEN THE TIME
COMES THAT WE NEED TO DO SO.

219
00:11:06,373 --> 00:11:08,106
-OH, DEAR.

220
00:11:08,106 --> 00:11:10,073
THEY'VE FINALLY BEGUN
TO GO INTO ACTION!

221
00:11:10,073 --> 00:11:12,539
IF THEY DO THAT,
THE STORY WILL STOP!

222
00:11:12,539 --> 00:11:14,006
OH, NOT GOOD.

223
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:18,306
THIS IS EXTREMELY BAD NEWS,
INDEED, LITTLE DUCK!

224
00:11:18,306 --> 00:11:23,273
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "MARCH"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

225
00:11:33,616 --> 00:11:36,316
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

226
00:11:37,168 --> 00:11:39,302
-SAY, FAKIR, I'VE BEEN THINKING,

227
00:11:39,302 --> 00:11:41,068
AND I'VE DECIDED
I'M GONNA HELP YOU.

228
00:11:41,068 --> 00:11:42,502
-HUH?
-WELL, 'CAUSE

229
00:11:42,502 --> 00:11:44,935
THAT'S THE ONLY THING
I CAN DO RIGHT NOW.

230
00:11:44,935 --> 00:11:47,968
SO I'M JUST GONNA DO WHAT I CAN
WITH ALL I'VE GOT.

231
00:11:47,968 --> 00:11:49,702
IF THERE'S SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH,

232
00:11:49,702 --> 00:11:51,435
TELL ME, NO MATTER WHAT IT IS.

233
00:11:51,435 --> 00:11:54,242
BUT ISN'T THERE SOMETHING WEIRD
ABOUT THAT AUTOR GUY?

234
00:11:54,242 --> 00:11:55,508
I WONDER IF THIS IS OKAY?

235
00:11:55,508 --> 00:11:57,242
-WEIRD OR NOT,
WE HAVE NO CHOICE.

236
00:11:57,242 --> 00:11:59,408
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

237
00:11:59,408 --> 00:12:01,642
-NO ENTOURAGE.

238
00:12:01,642 --> 00:12:04,542
-WHAT? YOU MEAN ME, MR. AUTOR?
I JUST --

239
00:12:04,542 --> 00:12:07,242
-I WON'T REPEAT MYSELF.
-MNH-MNH.

240
00:12:07,242 --> 00:12:10,842
-THINGS RELATING TO DROSSELMEYER
ARE GATHERED INSIDE THIS HOUSE.

241
00:12:10,842 --> 00:12:12,342
IT IS A HOLY PLACE.

242
00:12:12,342 --> 00:12:15,942
-OHHH, ARE YOU
THE WEIRD AUTOR, ZURA?

243
00:12:15,942 --> 00:12:18,842
-PEOPLE LIKE YOU TWO,
WHO ARE TOTALLY UNRELATED,

244
00:12:18,842 --> 00:12:20,375
AREN'T ALLOWED INSIDE!

245
00:12:20,375 --> 00:12:21,942
NOW COME, FAKIR.

246
00:12:21,942 --> 00:12:24,908
-WHAT? UNRELATED?
-[ CHUCKLES ]

247
00:12:24,908 --> 00:12:27,775
-PLEASE TAKE UZURA AND GO HOME.
-OH. MM-HMM.

248
00:12:31,075 --> 00:12:33,075
GOOD LUCK, FAKIR.

249
00:12:33,075 --> 00:12:35,842
-THIS IS DROSSELMEYER'S STUDY,

250
00:12:35,842 --> 00:12:38,575
PERFECTLY RE-CREATED
FROM THE DATA I GATHERED --

251
00:12:38,575 --> 00:12:40,442
PAPER-MADE
FROM 10-YEAR OLD REEDS,

252
00:12:40,442 --> 00:12:43,075
BLUE AND BLACK INK
AT A 7-TO-3 RATIO.

253
00:12:43,075 --> 00:12:44,475
THE FEATHER OF A WHITE SWAN

254
00:12:44,475 --> 00:12:47,042
THAT'S CROSSED THE SEA
THREE TIMES IS BEST FOR THE PEN,

255
00:12:47,042 --> 00:12:50,408
BUT FOR THIS PEN,
I SUBSTITUTED A DUCK'S FEATHER.

256
00:12:50,408 --> 00:12:51,642
-SO, THEN...

257
00:12:51,642 --> 00:12:54,348
AAH!

258
00:12:54,348 --> 00:12:55,715
WHAT WAS THAT FOR?

259
00:12:55,715 --> 00:12:57,648
-RITUAL ABLUTIONS.

260
00:12:57,648 --> 00:13:00,482
THEY SAY DROSSELMEYER ALWAYS
CLEANSED HIS BODY WITH WATER

261
00:13:00,482 --> 00:13:02,215
BEFORE HE WROTE HIS STORIES.

262
00:13:02,215 --> 00:13:04,415
DIDN'T YOU KNOW?
-WHY SHOULD I?

263
00:13:04,415 --> 00:13:06,448
-A DIRECT DESCENDANT
OF DROSSELMEYER'S,

264
00:13:06,448 --> 00:13:08,982
AND THIS IS YOUR LEVEL?

265
00:13:08,982 --> 00:13:11,982
-A DIRECT DESCENDANT
OF DROSSELMEYER?

266
00:13:11,982 --> 00:13:13,315
-OH, NO.

267
00:13:13,315 --> 00:13:14,448
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO SAY

268
00:13:14,448 --> 00:13:16,348
YOU DIDN'T KNOW THAT EITHER,
ARE YOU?

269
00:13:16,348 --> 00:13:18,115
IT'S A FACT ABOUT YOURSELF!

270
00:13:18,115 --> 00:13:19,815
YOU REALLY TAKE THE CAKE.

271
00:13:20,782 --> 00:13:23,348
THIS IS A DROSSELMEYER
FAMILY TREE

272
00:13:23,348 --> 00:13:25,782
THAT I DREW
AFTER MY OWN RESEARCH.

273
00:13:25,782 --> 00:13:27,315
LOOK.

274
00:13:27,315 --> 00:13:31,282
DROSSELMEYER'S HERE,
AND HERE YOU ARE.

275
00:13:31,282 --> 00:13:34,682
I BELIVE I'M PROBABLY CONNECTED
THIS WAY FROM THIS BRANCH,

276
00:13:34,682 --> 00:13:37,548
BUT I DON'T HAVE
ALL THE EVIDENCE YET.

277
00:13:37,548 --> 00:13:39,348
BUT THE ONE
WHO HELPED MY FATHER

278
00:13:39,348 --> 00:13:42,282
WHEN HE WAS LOST AS A BOY
IS THIS PERSON WRITTEN HERE.

279
00:13:42,282 --> 00:13:44,748
I KNOW THAT MUCH.

280
00:13:44,748 --> 00:13:47,515
-[ Thinking ]
I HAVE DROSSELMEYER'S BLOOD.

281
00:13:47,515 --> 00:13:49,282
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

282
00:13:49,282 --> 00:13:51,815
DOES THAT MEAN THOSE BOOKS
MISSING THEIR ENDINGS

283
00:13:51,815 --> 00:13:54,522
ARE THINGS
THAT DROSSELMEYER WROTE?

284
00:13:55,788 --> 00:13:59,488
THEN THE FACT THAT I SAW
ONE OF THOSE ENDINGS IS...

285
00:13:59,488 --> 00:14:01,922
[ BELL TOLLS ]

286
00:14:03,822 --> 00:14:05,922
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

287
00:14:07,988 --> 00:14:10,088
-[ Thinking ]
FAKIR HASN'T COME BACK

288
00:14:10,088 --> 00:14:12,288
FROM AUTOR'S HOUSE SINCE THEN.

289
00:14:12,288 --> 00:14:15,355
I'M...I'M JUST WAITING.

290
00:14:15,355 --> 00:14:18,488
OHH!
-EVERYBODY, PAY ATTENTION!

291
00:14:18,488 --> 00:14:20,888
-HUH?!
-TODAY MS. RUE AND MR. MYTHO

292
00:14:20,888 --> 00:14:23,322
WILL DEMONSTRATE THE ART
OF DANCE PARTNERING.

293
00:14:23,322 --> 00:14:24,488
-[ GASPS ]

294
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:27,522
[ SLOW, CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

295
00:14:31,988 --> 00:14:33,655
-ALL OF YOU, PLEASE,

296
00:14:33,655 --> 00:14:36,988
WATCH MS. RUE'S POINTE-WORK
VERY CLOSELY.

297
00:14:36,988 --> 00:14:38,622
AH!

298
00:14:40,655 --> 00:14:43,655
-[ Thinking ]
I'M JUST WATCHING AGAIN.

299
00:14:43,655 --> 00:14:45,688
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

300
00:14:53,595 --> 00:14:55,595
-AH.
-AH.

301
00:14:55,595 --> 00:14:56,662
-RUE.

302
00:14:59,395 --> 00:15:01,928
-[ YOWLS ]

303
00:15:01,928 --> 00:15:03,995
-[ GASPS ]

304
00:15:03,995 --> 00:15:06,295
[ WHIMPERS ] THAT HURTS!

305
00:15:06,295 --> 00:15:07,562
[ THUD ]
[ ALL GASP ]

306
00:15:07,562 --> 00:15:10,562
-MS. RUE!
-YOU HESITATED TO TAKE MY HAND.

307
00:15:10,562 --> 00:15:12,528
CAN YOU REALLY SAY YOU LOVE ME?!

308
00:15:13,795 --> 00:15:16,028
-NO WAY!
-A BREAKUP!

309
00:15:16,028 --> 00:15:18,062
-RUE, ARE YOU OKAY?
-[ CRIES ]

310
00:15:18,062 --> 00:15:19,428
-MS. RUE!

311
00:15:19,428 --> 00:15:21,162
MR. MYTHO, WHAT'S WRONG?

312
00:15:21,162 --> 00:15:22,695
AREN'T YOU TWO GETTING MA--
UH...

313
00:15:22,695 --> 00:15:25,695
-WHAT'S GOING ON?
DID I MISS SOMETHING?

314
00:15:25,695 --> 00:15:28,028
-[ Thinking ]
IT LOOKS LIKE IT WAS TOO SOON

315
00:15:28,028 --> 00:15:31,028
FOR MR. MYTHO
TO GET MARRIED AFTER ALL.

316
00:15:31,028 --> 00:15:35,528
A DAY MAY COME WHEN SPECIAL
MARRIAGE TRAINING IS NECESSARY.

317
00:15:39,328 --> 00:15:41,895
-[ SIGHS ]

318
00:15:41,895 --> 00:15:45,062
[ Thinking ]
MYTHO WAS ALWAYS KIND TO RUE,

319
00:15:45,062 --> 00:15:48,595
BUT HE'S CHANGING MORE AND MORE.

320
00:15:48,595 --> 00:15:52,102
FAKIR! FAKIR!

321
00:15:52,102 --> 00:15:53,502
-WOULD YOU BE QUIET?

322
00:15:53,502 --> 00:15:55,902
-UM, IS FAKIR...

323
00:15:55,902 --> 00:15:59,502
OH. FAKIR?

324
00:15:59,502 --> 00:16:01,368
OH! FAKIR, HANG ON!

325
00:16:01,368 --> 00:16:03,035
HANG IN THERE!

326
00:16:03,035 --> 00:16:04,735
WHAT DID YOU DO TO HIM?

327
00:16:04,735 --> 00:16:06,302
-NOTHING.
-LIAR!

328
00:16:06,302 --> 00:16:07,668
-IT'S TRUE.

329
00:16:07,668 --> 00:16:09,668
HE'S BEEN STANDING THERE
THREE DAYS,

330
00:16:09,668 --> 00:16:11,868
NOT EATING, NOT SLEEPING --
NOTHING.

331
00:16:11,868 --> 00:16:13,135
-WHY DID YOU MAKE HIM DO THAT?!

332
00:16:13,135 --> 00:16:15,768
-HE'LL BE ABLE TO HONE HIS MIND
THIS WAY.

333
00:16:15,768 --> 00:16:17,635
IF HE CAN'T EVEN ENDURE THIS,

334
00:16:17,635 --> 00:16:19,002
HE'S A LOST CAUSE.

335
00:16:19,002 --> 00:16:20,802
-YOU KNOW, YOU'RE HORRIBLE!

336
00:16:20,802 --> 00:16:23,068
-I'M FINE.
-FAKIR?

337
00:16:23,068 --> 00:16:25,368
-THEN STOP LYING ON THE FLOOR
AND STAND.

338
00:16:25,368 --> 00:16:27,368
TONIGHT WE WILL TEST
YOUR APTITUDE.

339
00:16:27,368 --> 00:16:30,991
KEEP GOING UNTIL THEN.
-HMM.

340
00:16:35,005 --> 00:16:37,371
-HERE IN GOLD CROWN TOWN,

341
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:39,738
THERE'S AN OAK TREE
THAT THEY SAY THE TALE SPINNERS

342
00:16:39,738 --> 00:16:42,838
USED TO TEST THEMSELVES
A VERY LONG TIME AGO.

343
00:16:42,838 --> 00:16:44,171
IF YOU TOUCH THAT OAK

344
00:16:44,171 --> 00:16:46,171
WHEN THE BELL HAS JUST
FINISHED TOLLING MIDNIGHT,

345
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:50,338
YOU SHOULD BE ABLE TO HEAR
ITS VOICE IF YOU HAVE THE POWER.

346
00:16:50,338 --> 00:16:52,105
THAT'S THE PROOF OF YOUR GIFT.

347
00:16:52,105 --> 00:16:54,638
INCIDENTALLY, I CLEARLY
HEARD THE TREE MAKE A SOUND

348
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:56,845
LIKE A FAINT SIGH.

349
00:16:56,845 --> 00:16:58,978
WITHOUT THE POWER,

350
00:16:58,978 --> 00:17:01,578
SOMEONE WOULD LIKELY THINK
IT WAS JUST THE WIND.

351
00:17:01,578 --> 00:17:03,578
-BUT WHERE IS THE OAK TREE?

352
00:17:03,578 --> 00:17:05,845
-YOU'RE QUITE OBSERVANT.

353
00:17:05,845 --> 00:17:08,245
THE OAK TREE
WAS FELLED LONG AGO.

354
00:17:08,245 --> 00:17:11,845
ITS ROOTS ALONE ARE SLEEPING
BENEATH THIS MUSEUM.

355
00:17:11,845 --> 00:17:15,311
AND ONE OF THE STONES
STREWN HERE IS THE SOLE ENTRANCE

356
00:17:15,311 --> 00:17:18,045
THROUGH WHICH THE OAK TREE
CAN BE CONTACTED.

357
00:17:18,045 --> 00:17:21,411
ALTHOUGH EVEN I HAD SOME TROUBLE
FINDING WHICH STONE IT WAS.

358
00:17:21,411 --> 00:17:23,545
I'LL TELL YOU AS A SPECIAL --
-HUH?

359
00:17:27,611 --> 00:17:30,278
-[ GASPS ]

360
00:17:30,278 --> 00:17:31,678
I'M IMPRESSED.

361
00:17:31,678 --> 00:17:33,645
JUST WHAT YOU'D EXPECT
FROM A DIRECT DESCENDANT.

362
00:17:33,645 --> 00:17:36,245
I GUESS I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.
-HUH?

363
00:17:36,245 --> 00:17:39,278
-THAT'S THE SOLE POSITION FROM
WHICH YOU CAN HEAR THE OAK TREE.

364
00:17:39,278 --> 00:17:40,711
BUT BE PREPARED --

365
00:17:40,711 --> 00:17:43,445
THERE ARE ALSO MANY
WHO HAVE MESSED UP THE CONTACT

366
00:17:43,445 --> 00:17:45,778
AND GOTTEN SUCKED IN
BY THE TREE,

367
00:17:45,778 --> 00:17:48,211
ULTIMATELY LOSING THEIR LIVES.
-NO WAY!

368
00:17:48,211 --> 00:17:50,711
FAKIR, MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T
AFTER ALL.

369
00:17:50,711 --> 00:17:52,411
-[ SCOFFS ]
WEREN'T YOU THE ONE

370
00:17:52,411 --> 00:17:54,211
WHO TOLD ME
TO HURRY UP AND WRITE?

371
00:17:54,211 --> 00:17:56,311
-I'M SORRY, FAKIR! I'M SORRY!

372
00:17:56,311 --> 00:17:58,618
I DIDN'T THINK IT WAS THIS BIG,
MAJOR THING! I DIDN'T KNOW!

373
00:17:58,618 --> 00:18:01,118
I THOUGHT IT WAS JUST WRITING!
BUT -- BUT NOW --

374
00:18:01,118 --> 00:18:04,385
-MIDNIGHT.
[ BELL TOLLS ]

375
00:18:06,918 --> 00:18:08,851
-FAKIR! BUT --
-DON'T GET IN THE WAY!

376
00:18:08,851 --> 00:18:10,718
-NO, FAKIR! STOP!

377
00:18:14,185 --> 00:18:15,151
[ GASPS ]

378
00:18:16,185 --> 00:18:19,185
-[ HOWLS ]

379
00:18:19,185 --> 00:18:21,185
[ HOWLING CONTINUES ]

380
00:18:21,185 --> 00:18:22,585
-HMM.
-[ GASPS ]

381
00:18:22,585 --> 00:18:24,551
-SEEMS IT WAS NO GOOD AFTER ALL.

382
00:18:24,551 --> 00:18:26,285
HEY.

383
00:18:26,285 --> 00:18:28,785
HEY, YOU SHOULD JUST GIVE UP
ALREADY AND...

384
00:18:28,785 --> 00:18:29,818
AAH!

385
00:18:29,818 --> 00:18:31,185
[ GRUNTS ]

386
00:18:31,185 --> 00:18:32,585
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

387
00:18:32,585 --> 00:18:34,251
-FAKIR!

388
00:18:34,251 --> 00:18:36,285
FAKIR?

389
00:18:36,285 --> 00:18:38,518
FAKIR!

390
00:18:38,518 --> 00:18:41,185
-WHAT YOU CAN SEE,
CANNOT BE SEEN.

391
00:18:41,185 --> 00:18:43,918
WHAT YOU CAN HEAR,
MAKES NO SOUND.

392
00:18:43,918 --> 00:18:46,051
SEE WHAT CANNOT BE SEEN.

393
00:18:46,051 --> 00:18:47,651
HEAR WHAT CANNOT BE HEARD.

394
00:18:47,651 --> 00:18:49,085
-WHO ARE YOU?

395
00:18:49,085 --> 00:18:52,218
-SUBMERGE YOURSELF
IN THE BOG OF TRUTH

396
00:18:52,218 --> 00:18:54,751
THAT LIES FAR, FAR AWAY.

397
00:18:54,751 --> 00:18:56,425
-OHH. FAKIR?

398
00:18:59,091 --> 00:19:00,391
[ GASPS ]

399
00:19:00,391 --> 00:19:02,625
-[ GROANS ]

400
00:19:04,825 --> 00:19:06,025
-FAKIR!

401
00:19:06,025 --> 00:19:07,658
[ SPARKLE! ]
[ BUBBLE! BUBBLE! ]

402
00:19:07,658 --> 00:19:10,391
[ SPARKLE! SPARKLE! SPARKLE! ]

403
00:19:10,391 --> 00:19:12,858
[ PIANO PLAYING
UP-TEMPO CLASSICAL MUSIC ]

404
00:19:15,158 --> 00:19:16,358
[ SHIMMER! ]

405
00:19:16,358 --> 00:19:19,325
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

406
00:19:20,025 --> 00:19:22,525
-THIS SOUND. A CLOCK?

407
00:19:22,525 --> 00:19:24,691
[ TICKING ]

408
00:19:24,691 --> 00:19:26,558
NO.

409
00:19:26,558 --> 00:19:27,891
THIS IS...

410
00:19:27,891 --> 00:19:29,658
[ HEARTBEAT ]
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

411
00:19:29,658 --> 00:19:31,991
...A HEARTBEAT.

412
00:19:33,758 --> 00:19:36,525
-FAKIR, PLEASE,
YOU MUST WAKE UP.

413
00:19:36,525 --> 00:19:39,291
DON'T LET THE OAK TREE
SUCK YOU IN.

414
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:40,991
-I...

415
00:19:40,991 --> 00:19:42,658
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

416
00:19:42,658 --> 00:19:45,591
-EVERYTHING IS ONE,
ONE IS EVERYTHING.

417
00:19:45,591 --> 00:19:48,391
ALL STORIES ARE SPUN INTO ONE.

418
00:19:48,391 --> 00:19:52,391
THE BEGINNING IS THE END,
THE END IS THE BEGINNING.

419
00:19:52,391 --> 00:19:55,498
-FAKIR, ANSWER ME.

420
00:19:55,498 --> 00:19:57,898
FAKIR.

421
00:19:57,898 --> 00:19:58,965
PLEASE COME BACK.

422
00:20:01,698 --> 00:20:03,965
-THE START IS
A HAPPY ACCIDENT --

423
00:20:03,965 --> 00:20:06,365
THE END, THE FATE
FOR WHICH IT'S MEANT.

424
00:20:06,365 --> 00:20:07,931
EXISTENCE IS FALSE.

425
00:20:07,931 --> 00:20:09,531
TRUTH IS NOTHINGNESS.

426
00:20:09,531 --> 00:20:10,998
-YES, YOU'RE RIGHT.

427
00:20:10,998 --> 00:20:12,298
ALL GO TO NOTHING...

428
00:20:12,298 --> 00:20:16,265
IN THE END, BECOMING ONE
WITH EVERYTHING ELSE.

429
00:20:16,265 --> 00:20:19,531
I WILL WATCH OVER EVERYONE
IN THIS WAY

430
00:20:19,531 --> 00:20:22,631
AND GO TOWARDS
THE ETERNAL ENDING.

431
00:20:22,631 --> 00:20:26,565
-TO THOSE WHO ACCEPT EVERYTHING,
HAPPINESS.

432
00:20:26,565 --> 00:20:29,698
TO THOSE WHO RESIST EVERYTHING,
GLORY.

433
00:20:32,298 --> 00:20:34,531
[ RUMBLING ]

434
00:20:34,531 --> 00:20:35,931
-[ GASPS ] FAKIR!

435
00:20:35,931 --> 00:20:39,398
-TO THOSE WHO ACCEPT EVERYTHING,
HAPPINESS.

436
00:20:39,398 --> 00:20:41,865
-FAKIR! FAKIR!

437
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:43,998
FAKIR, ANSWER ME.

438
00:20:43,998 --> 00:20:45,531
LET ME HEAR YOUR VOICE.

439
00:20:45,531 --> 00:20:49,631
-TO THOSE WHO RESIST EVERYTHING,
GLORY.

440
00:20:51,465 --> 00:20:52,698
-DUCK.

441
00:20:52,698 --> 00:20:55,705
-ANSWER ME, FAKIR.

442
00:20:55,705 --> 00:20:58,538
[ SOBBING ]

443
00:21:00,871 --> 00:21:02,338
-AHH!

444
00:21:02,338 --> 00:21:05,338
-FAKIR!

445
00:21:05,338 --> 00:21:10,305
-HE -- HE WAS...CHOSEN.

446
00:21:11,838 --> 00:21:14,071
-I'M SORRY, FAKIR.

447
00:21:14,071 --> 00:21:16,438
I COULDN'T DO ANYTHING.

448
00:21:16,438 --> 00:21:18,105
NOTHING.

449
00:21:18,105 --> 00:21:20,338
-I HEARD A VOICE.

450
00:21:20,338 --> 00:21:23,738
IT WAS YOURS.

451
00:21:23,738 --> 00:21:25,771
[ PIANO PLAYING
CLASSICAL MUSIC ]

452
00:21:27,738 --> 00:21:31,071
-SOMEDAY, THE PRINCE
WILL BECOME MY PRINCE ALONE.

453
00:21:31,071 --> 00:21:33,571
-WHAT AM I?

454
00:21:33,571 --> 00:21:35,938
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

455
00:21:35,938 --> 00:21:38,571
SHOULD I LOVE?

456
00:21:38,571 --> 00:21:40,205
CAN I LOVE?

457
00:21:40,205 --> 00:21:41,571
IF SO, HOW?

458
00:21:41,571 --> 00:21:43,571
NO! I WILL <i>BE</i> LOVED!

459
00:21:43,571 --> 00:21:46,005
LOVE ME! LOVE ME AND ME ALONE!

460
00:21:46,005 --> 00:21:48,505
EVERYONE, THROW AWAY YOUR LIVES
AND LOVE ME!

461
00:21:48,505 --> 00:21:49,805
-THIS IS BAD.

462
00:21:49,805 --> 00:21:53,138
THE STORY'S TURNED TRAGIC
JUST AS I WANTED IT TO,

463
00:21:53,138 --> 00:21:56,545
BUT WHAT GOOD IS IT
IF THEY STOP IT BEFORE THE END?

